Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Justice Point Pretrial Services Report received and filed.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief, filed.
Plea Questionnaire Waiver of Rights and Addendum, filed.

Defendant Timothy Louis Jackson in court.  Attorney Nathan Francis Opland-Dobs in court for Timothy Louis Jackson.  Attorney Elaine B. Fehrs in court for State of Wisconsin. Deputy Court Clerk: SD. 
Final Pretrial held.  Defense counsel recently received an offer and requests plea and sentencing date.  Court vacates previously scheduled jury trial date.  Case adjourned, Br. 41.
Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for November 21, 2022 at 02:00 pm.
State's Witness List, received and filed.
State's Motions in Limine, received and filed.
Defendant's Witness List, received and filed.
Defendant's Requested Jury Instructions, received and filed.

Defendant Timothy Louis Jackson in court with attorney Nathan Francis Opland-Dobs.  Gerald Henry Alder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Case in court for scheduling conference. Case is in trial posture, defense counsel requests case be placed on the trial calendar. Any pretrial motions to be filed a week before the final pretrial date. Case adjourned to Branch 35. Parties are advised that effective August 1, 2022 this case will be assigned to Judge Audrey Skwierawski, Branch 41 in Room 501 of the Courthouse.  Final pre-trial scheduled for September 14, 2022 at 08:30 am.  Jury trial scheduled for October 10, 2022 at 09:00 am.

CASE HEARD FOR BR. 35:
Defendant Timothy Louis Jackson in court with attorney Nathan Francis Opland-Dobs.  Samantha Raygo appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: P.O. Terrance Island - MPD.   State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 35.  Scheduling conference scheduled for May 5, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Court ordered no contact with T.C.O,D.R.E and S.N.J
No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for Level 5 Supervision with Electronic Monitoring. If electronic monitoring device is unavailable defendant to be released and placed on the waiting list.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Timothy Louis Jackson in court with attorney Nathan Francis Opland-Dobs.  Defendant Timothy Louis Jackson in custody.  Jon R Josephsen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Timothy Louis Jackson appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Rosa, Branch 35.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Defense enters a plea of NOT GUILTY as to misdemeanor counts 2 and 3. Commissioner advised DNA sample has NOT been obtained from the Defendant.  Court ordered the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department to obtain DNA sample from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4). 
This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for April 6, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.`
